cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the intersection of game theory and distributed computing, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper focuses on the dynamics of decentralized environments, categories such as cs.GT and cs.DC are more likely to be the primary categories. The other categories are also relevant due to the various applications mentioned in the abstract.
